                This might backfire horribly, but we don’t really want to limit your imagination, so just make sure to follow these basic rules:
              </p>
              <p>
               <ul>
                <li>We will only consider integrations that work with the Toggl Button Chrome extension</li>
                <li>Your integration has to be approved (read: actually working, not “theoretical”, not FUBAR) by our staff</li>
                <li>That’s because integrations that pass the bar become officially featured Toggl Button integrations</li>
                <li>You can submit your pull requests <b>until February 14th.</b></li>
                <li>Grand prize (iPad + Raspberry Pi) awarded to one lucky random contributor for approved integration.</li>
                <li>Second prize (Raspberry Pi) awarded to the weirdest/coolest/most useful integration as voted by our staff.</li>
                <li>Winners will be announced on February 22nd on our <a href="https://www.facebook.com/Toggl" target="_blank">Facebook</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/Toggl" target="_blank">Twitter</a> and GitHub.</li>
                <li>We do reserve the right to not add an integration if it makes us go “NO JUST NO”</li>
                <li>We will not add integrations with porn sites</li>
                <li>We <i>might</i> add integrations with FarmVille</li>
               </ul>
              </p>
